Exercise 2: Load City from Spring XML
Description:
This program demonstrates loading a City object from an XML configuration using Spring's ClassPathXmlApplicationContext.

Sample Input (in beans.xml):

<bean id="city" class="com.example.demo.City">
    <property name="name" value="Bengaluru"/>
    <property name="state" value="Karnataka"/>
</bean>

Output:

City Name: Bengaluru  
State: Karnataka

Tech Used:
Spring Core (ApplicationContext)

XML Bean Configuration

Java POJO (City.java)
